  "notes": "Proto-Gulf Arabic — abstract ancestor node for Kuwaiti, Bahraini, Qatari, and Emirati Arabic. DEFINING FEATURE: k → /tʃ/ before front vowels (/i, iː, e/). ق → /ɡ/ (Bedouin/traditional Gulf). θ, ð often preserved. Vowel imāla prominent. Holes (1990) is the primary reference grammar.",
